{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":440,"text":"I'm Ellen and I'm totally\nobsessed with food."},{"time":3560,"text":"But I didn't start out obsessed with food."},{"time":5584,"text":"I started out obsessed\nwith global security policy,"},{"time":8060,"text":"because I lived in New York during 9/11\nand it was a very relevant thing."},{"time":11540,"text":"I got from global security policy to food"},{"time":13517,"text":"because I realized when I'm hungry,\nI'm really pissed off,"},{"time":16260,"text":"and I'm assuming\nthe rest of the world is too."},{"time":18460,"text":"Especially if you and your kids are hungry\nand your neighbor's kids are hungry"},{"time":22180,"text":"and your whole neighborhood is hungry."},{"time":24060,"text":"And actually, it looks like\nthe areas of the world that are hungry"},{"time":27240,"text":"are also the areas of the world\nthat are pretty insecure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29960,"text":"So I took a job at the United Nations\nWorld Food Programme"},{"time":32720,"text":"as a way to try to address\nthese security issues"},{"time":35000,"text":"through food security issues."},{"time":36440,"text":"There, I came across what I think\nis the most brilliant of their programs."},{"time":39957,"text":"It's called School Feeding\nand it's a really simple idea"},{"time":42606,"text":"to get in the middle\nof the cycle of poverty and hunger"},{"time":45210,"text":"that continues for a lot of people\naround the world, and stop it."},{"time":48327,"text":"A free school meal gets kids into school,"},{"time":50320,"text":"which is education,\nthe first step out of poverty,"},{"time":52720,"text":"but it also gives them the micronutrients\nand the macronutrients they need"},{"time":56240,"text":"to develop mentally and physically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57960,"text":"While I was working at the UN,\nI met this girl. Her name is Lauren Bush."},{"time":61400,"text":"And she had this really awesome idea\nto sell the bag, called the \"Feed Bag\" --"},{"time":65091,"text":"which is really beautifully ironic\nbecause you can strap on the Feed Bag."},{"time":68560,"text":"But each bag we'd sell would provide"},{"time":70320,"text":"a year's worth\nof school meals for one kid."},{"time":72880,"text":"It's so simple, and we thought, OK,"},{"time":74800,"text":"it costs between 20 and 50 bucks\nto provide school feeding for a year."},{"time":78200,"text":"We could sell these bags\nand raise a ton of money and awareness"},{"time":81280,"text":"for the World Food Programme."},{"time":82720,"text":"But at the UN,\nsometimes things move slowly"},{"time":84800,"text":"and they basically said no."},{"time":86160,"text":"And we thought, this is such a good idea,\nit's going to raise so much money."},{"time":89800,"text":"So we said screw it,\nwe'll start our own company,"},{"time":92160,"text":"which we did, three years ago."},{"time":93613,"text":"That was my first dream,\nto start this company called FEED,"},{"time":96440,"text":"and here's a screenshot of our website."},{"time":98360,"text":"We did a bag for Haiti\njust a month after the earthquake"},{"time":101040,"text":"to provide school meals for kids in Haiti."},{"time":103120,"text":"So FEED's doing great."},{"time":104360,"text":"We've so far provided 55 million meals\nto kids around the world"},{"time":107360,"text":"by selling now 550,000 bags,\na ton of bags, a lot of bags."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110800,"text":"All this time you're really --"},{"time":112560,"text":"hunger is a hard thing to think about,"},{"time":114440,"text":"because what we think about is eating."},{"time":116320,"text":"I think about eating a lot\nand I really love it."},{"time":118600,"text":"And the thing that's strange\nabout international hunger"},{"time":121240,"text":"and talking about international issues"},{"time":123120,"text":"is that most people want to know:"},{"time":124760,"text":"\"What are you doing for America's kids?\""},{"time":127240,"text":"There's definitely hunger in America:"},{"time":129280,"text":"49 million people\nand almost 16.7 million children."},{"time":131840,"text":"I mean that's pretty dramatic\nfor our own country."},{"time":134240,"text":"Hunger definitely means\nsomething different in America"},{"time":136800,"text":"than it does internationally,"},{"time":138240,"text":"but it's incredibly important\nto address hunger in our own country."},{"time":141440,"text":"But the bigger problem\nthat we all know about is obesity,"},{"time":144160,"text":"and it's dramatic."},{"time":145440,"text":"The other thing that's dramatic"},{"time":146960,"text":"is that both hunger and obesity\nhave really risen in the last 30 years."},{"time":150440,"text":"Unfortunately, obesity's\nnot only an American problem."},{"time":153040,"text":"It's actually been spreading\nall around the world"},{"time":155400,"text":"and mainly through our kind\nof food systems that we're exporting."},{"time":158480,"text":"The numbers are pretty crazy."},{"time":159920,"text":"There's a billion people\nobese or overweight"},{"time":162040,"text":"and a billion people hungry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163440,"text":"So those seem like\ntwo bifurcated problems,"},{"time":165720,"text":"but I kind of started\nto think about, you know,"},{"time":167960,"text":"what is obesity and hunger?"},{"time":169320,"text":"What are both those things about?"},{"time":170960,"text":"Well, they're both about food."},{"time":172440,"text":"And when you think about food,"},{"time":174440,"text":"the underpinning of food in both cases\nis potentially problematic agriculture."},{"time":179280,"text":"And agriculture is where food comes from."},{"time":182200,"text":"Agriculture in America's very interesting."},{"time":184240,"text":"It's very consolidated"},{"time":186000,"text":"and the foods that are produced\nlead to the foods that we eat."},{"time":188960,"text":"The foods that are produced are,\nmore or less, corn, soy and wheat."},{"time":192160,"text":"And that's three-quarters\nof the food that we're eating:"},{"time":194840,"text":"processed foods and fast foods."},{"time":196400,"text":"Unfortunately, in our agricultural system,"},{"time":198440,"text":"we haven't done a good job\nin the last three decades"},{"time":200920,"text":"of exporting those technologies\naround the world."},{"time":203280,"text":"So African agriculture, which is the place\nof most hunger in the world,"},{"time":206640,"text":"has actually fallen precipitously\nas hunger has risen."},{"time":209360,"text":"So somehow we're not making the connect"},{"time":211480,"text":"between exporting\na good agricultural system"},{"time":213840,"text":"that will help feed people\nall around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216120,"text":"Who is farming?\nThat's what I was wondering."},{"time":218440,"text":"So I went and stood\non a big grain bin in the Midwest,"},{"time":221080,"text":"and that really didn't help me\nunderstand farming,"},{"time":223480,"text":"but I think it's a really cool picture."},{"time":225400,"text":"And the reality is\nthat between farmers in America --"},{"time":228360,"text":"who actually, quite frankly,\nwhen I spend time in the Midwest,"},{"time":231320,"text":"are pretty large in general."},{"time":233080,"text":"And their farms are also large."},{"time":234920,"text":"But farmers in the rest of the world\nare actually quite skinny,"},{"time":237920,"text":"and that's because they're starving."},{"time":239659,"text":"Most hungry people in the world\nare subsistence farmers."},{"time":242320,"text":"And most of those people are women --"},{"time":244160,"text":"which is a totally other topic\nthat I won't get on right now,"},{"time":247080,"text":"but I'd love to do\nthe feminist thing at some point."},{"time":249560,"text":"I think it's really interesting to look\nat agriculture from these two sides."},{"time":253160,"text":"There's this large, consolidated farming\nthat's led to what we eat in America,"},{"time":256880,"text":"and it's really been since around 1980,\nafter the oil crisis,"},{"time":259880,"text":"when, you know -- mass consolidation,"},{"time":261720,"text":"mass exodus of small farmers\nin this country."},{"time":263960,"text":"And then in the same time period,"},{"time":265600,"text":"we've kind of left Africa's farmers\nto do their own thing."},{"time":268600,"text":"Unfortunately, what is farmed\nends up as what we eat."},{"time":271480,"text":"And in America, a lot of what we eat\nhas led to obesity"},{"time":274520,"text":"and has led to a real change"},{"time":276520,"text":"in sort of what our diet is,\nin the last 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279640,"text":"It's crazy."},{"time":280880,"text":"A fifth of kids under two drinks soda."},{"time":283760,"text":"Hello! You don't put soda in bottles."},{"time":285760,"text":"But people do, because it's so cheap,"},{"time":287760,"text":"and so our whole food system\nin the last 30 years has really shifted."},{"time":291040,"text":"I mean, you know,\nit's not just in our own country,"},{"time":293760,"text":"but really we're exporting\nthe system around the world,"},{"time":296720,"text":"and when you look at the data\nof least developed countries --"},{"time":299640,"text":"especially in cities,\nwhich are growing really rapidly --"},{"time":303080,"text":"people are eating\nAmerican processed foods."},{"time":305400,"text":"And in one generation,\nthey're going from hunger"},{"time":307760,"text":"and all of the detrimental\nhealth effects of hunger"},{"time":310760,"text":"to obesity and things like diabetes\nand heart disease in one generation."},{"time":314400,"text":"So the problematic food system\nis affecting both hunger and obesity."},{"time":319080,"text":"Not to beat a dead horse,\nbut this is a global food system"},{"time":322280,"text":"where there's a billion people hungry\nand a billion people obese."},{"time":325400,"text":"I think that's the only way to look at it."},{"time":327480,"text":"And instead of taking these two things"},{"time":329360,"text":"as bifurcated problems\nthat are very separate,"},{"time":331560,"text":"it's really important\nto look at them as one system."},{"time":334480,"text":"We get a lot of our food\nfrom all around the world"},{"time":336880,"text":"and people from all around the world\nare importing our food system,"},{"time":340080,"text":"so it's incredibly relevant\nto start a new way of looking at it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343120,"text":"I've learned --\nand the technology people here,"},{"time":345400,"text":"which I'm totally not one of --"},{"time":346920,"text":"but apparently, it really takes 30 years"},{"time":348880,"text":"for a lot of technologies\nto become really endemic to us,"},{"time":351720,"text":"like the mouse\nand the Internet and Windows."},{"time":354240,"text":"You know, there's 30-year cycles."},{"time":355880,"text":"I think 2010 can be\na really interesting year"},{"time":358040,"text":"because it is the end\nof the 30-year cycle,"},{"time":360080,"text":"and it's the birthday\nof the global food system."},{"time":362360,"text":"That's the first birthday\nI want to talk about."},{"time":364600,"text":"If we really think that this is something\nthat's happened in the last 30 years,"},{"time":368360,"text":"there's hope in that."},{"time":369640,"text":"It's the 30th anniversary of GMO crops"},{"time":371520,"text":"and the Big Gulp, Chicken McNuggets,\nhigh-fructose corn syrup,"},{"time":374480,"text":"the farm crisis in America"},{"time":375760,"text":"and the change in how we've addressed\nagriculture internationally."},{"time":378920,"text":"So there's a lot of reasons\nto take this 30-year time period"},{"time":381800,"text":"as sort of the creation\nof this new food system."},{"time":384280,"text":"I'm not the only one who's obsessed\nwith this whole 30-year thing."},{"time":387440,"text":"The icons like Michael Pollan\nand Jamie Oliver in his TED Prize wish"},{"time":391160,"text":"both addressed this last\nthree-decade time period"},{"time":394120,"text":"as incredibly relevant\nfor food system change."},{"time":397160,"text":"Well, I really care about 1980"},{"time":398760,"text":"because it's also the 30th\nanniversary of me this year."},{"time":401920,"text":"And so in my lifetime,"},{"time":404600,"text":"a lot of what's happened in the world --"},{"time":406560,"text":"and being a person obsessed with food --"},{"time":408520,"text":"a lot of this has really changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410400,"text":"So my second dream is that I think\nwe can look to the next 30 years"},{"time":414520,"text":"as a time to change the food system again."},{"time":416960,"text":"And we know what's happened in the past,"},{"time":418920,"text":"so if we start now\nand we look at technologies"},{"time":421120,"text":"and improvements\nto the food system long-term,"},{"time":423320,"text":"we might be able\nto recreate the food system"},{"time":425440,"text":"so when I give my next talk\nand I'm 60 years old,"},{"time":427800,"text":"I'll be able to say\nthat it's been a success."},{"time":429960,"text":"So I'm announcing today\nthe start of a new organization,"},{"time":432640,"text":"or a new fund within the FEED Foundation,\ncalled the 30 Project."},{"time":435680,"text":"And the 30 Project is really focused"},{"time":437440,"text":"on these long-term ideas\nfor food system change."},{"time":440280,"text":"And I think by aligning international\nadvocates that are addressing hunger"},{"time":443800,"text":"and domestic advocates\nthat are addressing obesity,"},{"time":446240,"text":"we might actually look\nfor long-term solutions"},{"time":448600,"text":"that will make the food system\nbetter for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451040,"text":"We all tend to think\nthat these systems are quite different"},{"time":453840,"text":"and people argue whether or not\norganic can feed the world,"},{"time":456640,"text":"but if we take a 30-year view,\nthere's more hope in collaborative ideas."},{"time":460080,"text":"So I'm hoping that by connecting\nreally disparate organizations"},{"time":463080,"text":"like the ONE campaign and Slow Food,"},{"time":464840,"text":"which don't seem right now\nto have much in common,"},{"time":467240,"text":"we can talk about holistic,\nlong-term, systemic solutions"},{"time":470120,"text":"that will improve food for everyone."},{"time":472080,"text":"Some ideas I've had is like,\nlook, the reality is --"},{"time":474533,"text":"kids in the South Bronx\nneed apples and carrots"},{"time":477000,"text":"and so do kids in Botswana."},{"time":478680,"text":"And how are we going\nto get those kids those nutritious foods?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":481640,"text":"Another thing that's become incredibly\nglobal is production of meat and fish."},{"time":485320,"text":"Understanding how to produce protein"},{"time":487080,"text":"in a way that's healthy\nfor the environment"},{"time":489120,"text":"and healthy for people"},{"time":490400,"text":"will be incredibly important\nto address things like climate change"},{"time":493560,"text":"and how we use petrochemical fertilizers."},{"time":495640,"text":"And, you know, these are\nreally relevant topics"},{"time":497960,"text":"that are long-term and important"},{"time":499800,"text":"for both people in Africa\nwho are small farmers"},{"time":502880,"text":"and people in America\nwho are farmers and eaters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505440,"text":"And I also think that thinking\nabout processed foods in a new way,"},{"time":508960,"text":"where we actually\nprice the negative externalities"},{"time":511640,"text":"like petrochemicals\nand like fertilizer runoff"},{"time":514360,"text":"into the price of a bag of chips --"},{"time":516200,"text":"Well, if that bag of chips then becomes\ninherently more expensive than an apple,"},{"time":520880,"text":"then maybe it's time for a different sense\nof personal responsibility in food choice"},{"time":525080,"text":"because the choices are actually choices"},{"time":527040,"text":"instead of three-quarters of the products\nbeing made just from corn, soy and wheat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"The 30Project.org is launched"},{"time":532440,"text":"and I've gathered a coalition\nof a few organizations to start."},{"time":535400,"text":"And it'll be growing\nover the next few months."},{"time":537600,"text":"But I really hope\nthat you will all think of ways"},{"time":539960,"text":"that you can look long-term\nat things like the food system"},{"time":542720,"text":"and make change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543960,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}